questions.explanation: We have the given sequence, 84 LAST 67 CRAB 78 NEWS 89 ROSE 76 UNDO After, multiplying the digits of the word that is starting with consonant and ending at a consonant and adding the digits of the rest words within the number, we get: 32 LAST 42 CRAB 56 NEWS 17 ROSE 13 UNDO Arranging the words according to ascending order of the number from left to right end, we get 13 UNDO 17 ROSE 32 LAST 42 CRAB 56 NEWS Here, the 11th letter from left end is S.
